@guoger Markdown is better in general but RST has its good points. It allows for "note" boxes and is the only file format we currently have that allows for the creation of toc trees (it also does a better job with enumerated lists). 

In general I'd advise people to use markdown, since it's a more ubiquitous format, but if they want to use RST they have my blessing. 

Double backtics in markdown aren't ideal but they do work --- the extra backtics resolve themselves without an issue.

